news.title: Kerala government nears deal with DLF for Aspinwall House
news.para: The state had reportedly backed off from a similar deal on the waterfront heritage property, which has long served as the Biennale's main venue, earlier due to pricing disputes.

news.title: Lucknow development body to launch housing project in Gomtinagar Extension
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Prathamesh Kumar shared detailed plans for both projects during a meeting with stakeholders from the real estate sector on Friday.

news.title: Noida authority identifies illegal buildings across five villages
news.para: These buildings have been marked in red paint with the word "illegal," and official notices have been pasted to warn current occupants and prospective buyers.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body to raze 36 bungalows in Indrayani flood line at Chikhali
news.para: The lawyers claimed that the land purchased by the residents and the sale deeds were legal and there was only a dispute about the constructions.

news.title: Ludhiana: Allottees meet LIT officials over slow pace of work on Atal Apartments
news.para: Their major concern is the discrepancy between the payment they have made and progress of construction work. This project is expected to be completed in 2026.

news.title: Karnataka HC cancels illegal apartment society at Yelahanka Complex
news.para: In response, a group of affected residents filed a writ petition before the Karnataka High Court, challenging the legitimacy of the registration. Following several hearings, the High Court on May 2 delivered its verdict, setting aside the registration of the cooperative society.

news.title: MREAT rejects applications seeking condonation of AREPL's delay in filing appeals
news.para: MahaRERA had, in an order on Jul 29, 2024, directed AREPL to pay interest to home buyers who had invested in the ‘Immensa D' project of Kalpataru in Thane for the delay in handing over possession of flats.

news.title: Mumbai: Supreme Construction's director gets bail in PMLA case
news.para: Tekchandani had sought bail on the ground of delay in commencement of trial. The case is at the stage of framing charges. Special judge for cases under Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) A C Daga allowed his bail plea on May 15.

news.title: India’s aging population spurs demand for holistic senior housing models
news.para: Industry leaders are seeing senior living not just as a housing segment, but as a comprehensive care ecosystem that merges medical, social, and emotional well-being.

news.title: UK's Landsec's property valuations miss expectations, bets on retail growth
news.para: UK's Landsec has been shedding non-core assets as growth in office space remains weaker in comparison to retail and residential counterparts after the pandemic.

news.title: NBCC sells 446 residential units in Aspire Silicon City for ₹1,467.93 crore
news.para: The funds will go towards repayment of bank loans as well as reducing the funding requirement of ongoing projects. Aspire Silicon City is a Supreme Court monitored project.

news.title: IWG plans to open 40 new centers by 2025-end, pushes for partnership model
news.para: IWG has recently introduced a partnership model. Operating the business has changed completely. Hence we are moving from being tenants to being partners.

news.title: Decision on number of civic bodies to govern Bengaluru after discussion: Karnataka CM
news.para: "The Greater Bengaluru Governance Act is coming into effect from today... a Bill on this was passed by both houses of the state legislature, and the Governor has given his assent to it," Siddaramaiah said.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body approves revised draft development plan
news.para: This is the first DP for Pimpri Chinchwad that encompasses all areas within PCMC limits, including those merged after the city's initial formation. The draft DP covers a total area of 173.24sqkm.

news.title: JPMorgan to open new office in Paris as headcount grows
news.para: The new office, located behind the bank's Paris headquarters in Place Vendome, will open in 2027, with employees expected to relocate from its other buildings.

news.title: Property owners in Bengaluru demand solutions as e-khata system fails to deliver
news.para: However, property owners, especially from the 110 villages and municipal councils that were added to the BBMP limits in 2008, have been facing a lot of problems. They have been waiting for months to get the e-khata certificates, they claimed.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit rises 25% to ₹1,368 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 7,283 crore in the March quarter of FY25, from Rs 6,937 crore in the corresponding quarter in FY24, LIC Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Part of land can’t be retained after sale deed is executed: Karnataka HC
news.para: Justice NS Sanjay Gowda, in a single-judge ruling, granted the petition by Keerthi Harmony Apartment Owners Association, nullifying the BBMP licence given to developer Hanumantha Reddy for apartment construction.

news.title: JSW Paints emerges as frontrunner to acquire Akzo India
news.para: Ending weeks of intense negotiations, the two have signed an exclusivity agreement for bilateral negotiations to finalise terms and documentation for a share purchase agreement before making a formal announcement.

news.title: Lakshmi Mittal buys luxury mansion in Dubai's Emirates Hills
news.para: The India-born billionaire snapped up a palatial home in a gated community known as the “Beverly Hills of Dubai,” said the people, who didn’t want to be identified speaking publicly about the purchase, adding the home sold earlier this year.
